com.facebook.buck.core.rulekey

Annotation Type ExcludeFromRuleKey


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Target(value={FIELD,METHOD})
public @interface ExcludeFromRuleKey
    Marks a field/method of a class explicitly excluded from rulekeys. Usage of this should be very rare. In general, we consider uses of it to indicate likely correctness problems. Instead annotate the field with @AddToRuleKey.

    • Required Element Summary

      Required Elements 
      Modifier and Type Required Element and Description
      Class<? extends CustomFieldInputsTag> inputs
      Indicates how inputs should be derived from this field.
      Class<? extends CustomFieldSerializationTag> serialization
      Indicates how serialization of this field should be handled.

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      Class<? extends CustomFieldDepsTag> deps
      Indicates how deps should be derived from this field.
      String reason
      This indicates the reason we exclude a value from rulekeys.
      boolean shouldReport
      We really do think that using this annotation indicates a likely source of problems.

    • Element Detail

      • serialization

        public abstract Class<? extends CustomFieldSerializationTag> serialization
        Indicates how serialization of this field should be handled. For default serialization, use DefaultFieldSerialization If serialization cannot possibly be supported, use ThrowingSerialization.

      • inputs

        public abstract Class<? extends CustomFieldInputsTag> inputs
        Indicates how inputs should be derived from this field. For default inputs derivation, use DefaultFieldInputs. If this field should not contribute to inputs, use IgnoredFieldInputs.

      • reason

        public abstract String reason
        This indicates the reason we exclude a value from rulekeys. It's currently only used for logging.
        Default:
        ""

      • deps

        public abstract Class<? extends CustomFieldDepsTag> deps
        Indicates how deps should be derived from this field. For default deps derivation, use DefaultFieldDeps. If this field should not contribute to deps, use IgnoredFieldDeps. If you would like to provide custom logic, see CustomFieldDeps.
        Default:
        com.facebook.buck.core.rulekey.IgnoredFieldDeps.class

      • shouldReport

        public abstract boolean shouldReport
        We really do think that using this annotation indicates a likely source of problems. By default, the first time we encounter such an annotated field/method, we will log that information to the buck log.
        Default:
        true
